  "texts": [
    "4 For a fair comparison to MPGAN we use the same train and test splits chosen in Ref.",
    "PC-JeDi architecture and trainingPC-JeDi is a conditional score-based diffusion model trained to predict the noise added to a diffused particle cloud given two conditional properties of the jet, p jet T and m jet.",
    "The choice of neural network for the score model is open, though a desirable property for the set-to-set mapping is permutation equivariance.",
    "A wide variety of appropriate neural network architectures can be used for PC-JeDi including graph neural networks [82] and deep sets [83].",
    "For these studies, we use attention based transformers [84] which are an efficient and expressive class of neural networks based on the self-attention mechanism."
  ],
